Mota-Engil Wins $96.1 Million Contract to Build Mozambican Road, Pais Says

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-03-15T05:06:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/mota-engil-wins-96-1-million-contract-to-build-mozambican-road-pais-says.html
  Mota-Engil SGPS SA (EGL)  won a 69
million-euro ($96.1 million) tender to build a 250-kilometer
(155-mile) raod in central  Mozambique ,  O Pais  reported, citing
Francisco Itai Meque, governor of Zambezia province.  The project, which will employ 900 people, will connect the
central port of Quelimane to neighboring Malawi, the Maputo-
based newspaper said. Construction will begin in April and will
be completed in one year, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo via Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 